\section*{Value of the Data}




\begin{itemize}
\itemsep=0pt
\parsep=0pt
\item
These data facilitate the development of probabilistic methods for evaluating and quantifying similarity between pairs of striation mark evidence on fired bullets.

\item
Reproducibility is a critical component of work in forensic statistics, because it enables comparison between newly developed algorithms and established methods. Thus, other researchers in forensic statistics, and possibly forensic examiners who are interested in validating new methods, will benefit from these data being publicly available. Outside of forensic applications, researchers in statistics with violations of independence or researchers in machine learning may find this dataset useful because of its real-world relevance.

\item This data enables researchers to compare the method described in \citep{aoas} to other methods for analysis of bullet land scans, including those previously published, such as in \citet{cmps}, and methods developed in the future. In addition, this data has been used internally for validation of the method for use across other types of ammunition and other models of handguns; thus, experiments which examine the robustness of the model's application on external test sets may produce new insights by leveraging this data. %\svp{XXX It would also be possible to e.g. predict the change in the model's predictions based on updates to include new data sources, but I don't know whether we want to mention that...XXX}
