\item Open source algorithms supplemented by open data are a critical component of a fairer justice system, equally accessible to both prosecution and defense. Currently, many closed-source or closed-data algorithms are used to supplement the discretion of law enforcment agents and prosecutors, and these algorithms cannot be easily audited by affected parties. By making the source and intermediate data relating to this algorithm available, we are ensuring that the algorithm's details are fully transparent to all parties who may be affected by its use in forensic casework.
\end{itemize}

